1. Inheritance :
Inheriting the properties of existing class
2. Encapsulation:
Hiding the details
Possible through the access modifiers
(Private,Default,protected, and public)
Example: When we hit brake car should stop regardless of
any internal functionality being known to us
3.Polymorphism:
single interface can have multiple implementation
Eg. Wheel exist on every vehicles but the way they function can be different
Method over riding
4. Abstraction
Specific property that separates the objects.

